<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-01-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-01-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="372" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d372">
                        <head><persName type="from">Lord Lyons</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Seward</persName>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-01-28"><hi rend="italic">January</hi> 28, 1863.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> With reference to the correspondence which
                            has passed between us relative to the capture of the Elias Reed, I have
                            the honor to transmit to you an attested copy of an affidavit made by
                            two of the crew at Nassau. This document, has been sent to me by Messrs.
                            Saunders &amp; Son, of that place. I beg you to be so good as to return
                            it to me.</p>
                        <p>I have the honor to be, with the highest respect, sir, your most
                            obedient, humble servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>LYONS.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">W. H. Seward</hi>, <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>